# Rust SOP

- `cargo fmt` and `cargo clippy` (deny warnings) before commit when the project uses them.
- Prefer `Result` and `?` in libraries; document intentional `expect`/`unwrap` with invariants.
- Ownership: borrow when possible; `Arc`/`Mutex` only with clear lifetimes; avoid lock nesting.
- Async: Tokio at binary edge; `spawn` with structured shutdown; timeouts on external calls.
- Errors: use `thiserror`/`anyhow` per repo; map to user-safe messages at API boundary.
- Public API: minimal surface; hide modules; semver-aware breaking changes in CHANGELOG.
- Tests: unit in modules; integration in `tests/` against public API.
- Security: no `unsafe` without comment + review; sanitize lengths on external input.
- Acceptance: `cargo test` · `./scripts/test.sh` · `./scripts/verify.sh` when present.
